      "source": [
        "| Root Cause | Rows Affected | Proposed Strategy |\n",
        "|:-----------|:-------------:|:------------------|\n",
        "| No / zero purchase history | `{python} f\"{no_ph:,}\"` | Solution A — Agentic web search |\n",
        "| Very low history (1–4 units) | `{python} f\"{low_ph:,}\"` | Solution B — Similar-product transfer |\n",
        "| Price outside DBSCAN range | `{python} f\"{some_ph:,}\"` | Solution C — Threshold relaxation |\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Solution A — Agentic Web Search\n",
        "\n",
        "<div class=\"solution-cards\">\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-card sol-a\">\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-header\">\n",
        "  <div class=\"sol-icon\">🤖</div>\n",
        "  <div class=\"sol-top\">\n",
        "    <div class=\"sol-label\">Solution A · Zero-History Products</div>\n",
        "    <div class=\"sol-title\">Agentic Web Search with Citation</div>\n",
        "    <div class=\"sol-reach\">Targets <strong>`{python} f\"{no_ph:,}\"`</strong> rows with no purchase history</div>\n",
        "  </div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-body\">\n",
        "<p>When a product has no purchase history at all, Step 5 has no anchors. The only signal available is the product description, manufacturer, and catalog number. An agentic pipeline can autonomously enrich these rows:</p>\n",
        "<ul class=\"sol-steps\">\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"1\"><strong>Query construction</strong> — build a structured search from <code>RecognizedProductDesc</code>, <code>RecognizedManufacturerName</code>, and <code>RecognizedProductCatalogNumber</code>.</li>\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"2\"><strong>Search & extract</strong> — agent calls a web search tool or medical-device catalogue API and extracts candidate UOM labels and typical pack sizes.</li>\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"3\"><strong>Citation attachment</strong> — every suggestion is stored with its source URL so analysts can verify before accepting.</li>\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"4\"><strong>Confidence flagging</strong> — agent rates its own confidence (\"exact catalog number match\" vs. \"description keyword match\"). Low-confidence results require mandatory analyst sign-off before write-back.</li>\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"5\"><strong>Feedback loop</strong> — accepted suggestions are written to purchase history so future runs resolve the same products without a search.</li>\n",
        "</ul>\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-tags\">\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag effort-high\">High effort</span>\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag\">Requires analyst review</span>\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag\">Self-improving over time</span>\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag\">Needs prompt fine-tuning</span>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Solution B — Similar-Product Transfer\n",
        "\n",
        "<div class=\"solution-cards\">\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-card sol-b\">\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-header\">\n",
        "  <div class=\"sol-icon\">🔗</div>\n",
        "  <div class=\"sol-top\">\n",
        "    <div class=\"sol-label\">Solution B · Sparse History Products</div>\n",
        "    <div class=\"sol-title\">Purchase History Bridge via Product Similarity</div>\n",
        "    <div class=\"sol-reach\">Targets <strong>`{python} f\"{low_ph:,}\"`</strong> rows with 1–4 unit history</div>\n",
        "  </div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-body\">\n",
        "<p>Rather than going to the web, look inside existing purchase history for structurally similar products and borrow their ThresholdV2 clusters as a prior:</p>\n",
        "<ul class=\"sol-steps\">\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"1\"><strong>Similarity candidates</strong> — find products in the catalogue sharing the same <code>RecognizedManufacturerID</code>, same <code>RecognizedProductTypeID</code>, and similar description tokens (keyword overlap or embedding distance).</li>\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"2\"><strong>UOM profile transfer</strong> — the similar product's ThresholdV2 clusters and WAP are borrowed. The proximity scoring in Step 5 runs exactly as normal, using the borrowed thresholds.</li>\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"3\"><strong>Downgraded confidence</strong> — the resulting score is multiplied by a transfer discount factor (e.g., 0.80) to signal the assignment is inferred, not directly observed.</li>\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"4\"><strong>Analyst review queue</strong> — transferred rows surface in a separate queue for analysts to confirm the analogy is valid before the result propagates.</li>\n",
        "</ul>\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-tags\">\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag effort-med\">Medium effort</span>\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag\">Needs similarity criteria co-design with analysts</span>\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag\">No external API calls</span>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "\n",
        "### Key questions for analysts\n",
        "\n",
        "Before implementing, these must be answered collaboratively:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Does same **manufacturer + product type** constitute a strong enough analogy, or are there product categories where this would be systematically misleading?\n",
        "- What **discount factor** appropriately penalises borrowed confidence?\n",
        "- Are there clinical categories (implants vs. consumables) that require different similarity criteria?\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Solution C — Threshold Relaxation\n",
        "\n",
        "<div class=\"solution-cards\">\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-card sol-c\">\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-header\">\n",
        "  <div class=\"sol-icon\">⚙️</div>\n",
        "  <div class=\"sol-top\">\n",
        "    <div class=\"sol-label\">Solution C · Price Out-of-Range Products</div>\n",
        "    <div class=\"sol-title\">Widen the Proximity Window + Analyst Escalation</div>\n",
        "    <div class=\"sol-reach\">Targets <strong>`{python} f\"{some_ph:,}\"`</strong> rows with history but score &lt; 0.30</div>\n",
        "  </div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-body\">\n",
        "<p>These rows have adequate purchase history but the file's <code>PriceUOM</code> lands too far from every DBSCAN cluster. Common causes: supplier price changes, new pack sizes, or unit vs. case mismatches. Two complementary approaches:</p>\n",
        "<ul class=\"sol-steps\">\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"C1\"><strong>Widen LOG_EPS</strong> — raising <code>LOG_EPS</code> from 0.25 → 0.40 extends the tolerance from ~1.78× to ~2.51× price deviation. This is a global change; must be validated on a hold-out set to measure false-positive impact before deployment.</li>\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"C2\"><strong>Price-trend adjustment</strong> — for products with time-stamped history, detect upward/downward price trends and project cluster ranges forward. A product trending $10→$13→$16 is likely ~$19 today; the 12-month-old cluster misses it.</li>\n",
        "  <li data-n=\"C3\"><strong>Analyst escalation queue</strong> — rows where the best candidate scores 0.20–0.30 (just below acceptance) are surfaced to analysts with the best DBSCAN candidate and distance from the cluster edge visible. Fast accept/reject with feedback loops back to threshold calibration.</li>\n",
        "</ul>\n",
        "<div class=\"sol-tags\">\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag effort-low\">C1: Low effort (config change)</span>\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag effort-low\">C3: Low effort (UI change)</span>\n",
        "  <span class=\"sol-tag effort-med\">C2: Medium effort</span>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Coverage Comparison"
